SIMPLE: senatorial
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Senatorial
<hw>Sen`a*to"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>s⟦eacute⟧natorial</ets>, or L. <ets>senatorius</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a senator, or a senate; becoming to
a senator, or a senate; <as>as, <ex>senatorial</ex> duties;
<ex>senatorial</ex> dignity</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Entitled to elect a senator, or by senators; <as>as,
the <ex>senatorial</ex> districts of a State</as>.</def> <mark>[U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Senatorially</ent>⟦br⟧
